Republicans have voted repeatedly to protect Americans with pre-existing conditions including our first vote in 2019 - requiring the consideration of legislation that guarantees no American can be denied coverage or charged more because of pre-existing conditions. #ForThePolitics

These waivers work! Seven of the states that have created their own reinsurance programs under Section 1332 have seen lower premiums. On average, premiums have decreased 19.9% in the first year of enactment. #ForThePolitics

To be clear: the ACA pre-existing conditions provisions cannot be waived under section 1332.  These waivers give states flexibility to innovate, lower costs for all insured, including those with pre-existing conditions! #ForThePolitics
CMS Administrator Verma said: “Again, I want to make clear that a section 1332 waiver CANNOT undermine coverage for people with pre-existing conditions.”

Do not judge a bill by its name! Today, the house will vote on the H.R. 986 – Protecting Americans with Pre-existing Conditions Act, however, despite the name, this bill does NOTHING to protect people with pre-existing conditions.
